</disciplines><abstract>&lt;p&gt;The task of understanding the multiple aspects of learning environments and then attempting to make these environments more effective is a complex undertaking. Expansion of our personal awareness of various issues associated with learning environments depends on a willingness to consider new ideas and approaches. This means listening to the many &quot;voices&quot; that address the issues, being open to change in our personal practices, and raising new questions about teaching and learning.&lt;/p&gt;</abstract>
